label: b0ch
comment: Zero sequence shunt (charging) susceptance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

label: g0ch
comment: Zero sequence shunt (charging) conductance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

label: r0
comment: Zero sequence series resistance of the entire line section.

label: shortCircuitEndTemperature
comment: Maximum permitted temperature at the end of SC for the calculation of minimum short-circuit currents. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: x0
comment: Zero sequence series reactance of the entire line section.

label: converterFedDrive
comment: Indicates whether the machine is a converter fed drive. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: efficiency
comment: Efficiency of the asynchronous machine at nominal operation as a percentage. Indicator for converter drive motors. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: iaIrRatio
comment: Ratio of locked-rotor current to the rated current of the motor (Ia/Ir). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: polePairNumber
comment: Number of pole pairs of stator. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: ratedMechanicalPower
comment: Rated mechanical power (Pr in IEC 60909-0). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: reversible
comment: Indicates for converter drive motors if the power can be reversible. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: rxLockedRotorRatio
comment: Locked rotor ratio (R/X). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: ipMax
comment:
Maximum allowable peak short-circuit current of busbar (Ipmax in IEC 60909-0). 
Mechanical limit of the busbar in the substation itself. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: r
comment: Nominal resistance of device.

label: r
comment: Positive sequence Thevenin resistance.

label: r0
comment: Zero sequence Thevenin resistance.

label: rn
comment: Negative sequence Thevenin resistance.

label: x
comment: Positive sequence Thevenin reactance.

label: x0
comment: Zero sequence Thevenin reactance.

label: xn
comment: Negative sequence Thevenin reactance.

label: negativeR12
comment:
Negative sequence series resistance from terminal sequence  1 to terminal sequence 2. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: negativeR21
comment:
Negative sequence series resistance from terminal sequence 2 to terminal sequence 1. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: negativeX12
comment:
Negative sequence series reactance from terminal sequence  1 to terminal sequence 2. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
Usage : EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: negativeX21
comment:
Negative sequence series reactance from terminal sequence 2 to terminal sequence 1. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
Usage: EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: positiveR12
comment:
Positive sequence series resistance from terminal sequence  1 to terminal sequence 2 . Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909. 
EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: positiveR21
comment:
Positive sequence series resistance from terminal sequence 2 to terminal sequence 1. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: positiveX12
comment:
Positive sequence series reactance from terminal sequence  1 to terminal sequence 2. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
Usage : EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: positiveX21
comment:
Positive sequence series reactance from terminal sequence 2 to terminal sequence 1. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
Usage : EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: zeroR12
comment:
Zero sequence series resistance from terminal sequence  1 to terminal sequence 2. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: zeroR21
comment:
Zero sequence series resistance from terminal sequence  2 to terminal sequence 1. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
Usage : EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: zeroX12
comment:
Zero sequence series reactance from terminal sequence  1 to terminal sequence 2. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
Usage : EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: zeroX21
comment:
Zero sequence series reactance from terminal sequence 2 to terminal sequence 1. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
Usage : EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: r
comment:
Positive sequence resistance. Used to represent Extended-Ward (IEC 60909).
Usage : Extended-Ward is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: r0
comment:
Zero sequence resistance. Used to represent Extended-Ward (IEC 60909).
Usage : Extended-Ward is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: r2
comment:
Negative sequence resistance. Used to represent Extended-Ward (IEC 60909).
Usage : Extended-Ward is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: x
comment:
Positive sequence reactance. Used to represent Extended-Ward (IEC 60909).
Usage : Extended-Ward is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: x0
comment:
Zero sequence reactance. Used to represent Extended-Ward (IEC 60909).
Usage : Extended-Ward is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: x2
comment:
Negative sequence reactance. Used to represent Extended-Ward (IEC 60909).
Usage : Extended-Ward is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: ikSecond
comment: Indicates whether initial symmetrical short-circuit current and power have been calculated according to IEC (Ik").  Used only if short circuit calculations are done according to superposition method.

label: maxInitialSymShCCurrent
comment: Maximum initial symmetrical short-circuit currents (Ik" max) in A (Ik" = Sk"/(SQRT(3) Un)). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: maxR0ToX0Ratio
comment: Maximum ratio of zero sequence resistance of Network Feeder to its zero sequence reactance (R(0)/X(0) max). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: maxR1ToX1Ratio
comment: Maximum ratio of positive sequence resistance of Network Feeder to its positive sequence reactance (R(1)/X(1) max). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: maxZ0ToZ1Ratio
comment: Maximum ratio of zero sequence impedance to its positive sequence impedance (Z(0)/Z(1) max). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: minInitialSymShCCurrent
comment: Minimum initial symmetrical short-circuit currents (Ik" min) in A (Ik" = Sk"/(SQRT(3) Un)). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: minR0ToX0Ratio
comment: Indicates whether initial symmetrical short-circuit current and power have been calculated according to IEC (Ik"). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 6090.

label: minR1ToX1Ratio
comment: Minimum ratio of positive sequence resistance of Network Feeder to its positive sequence reactance (R(1)/X(1) min). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: minZ0ToZ1Ratio
comment: Minimum ratio of zero sequence impedance to its positive sequence impedance (Z(0)/Z(1) min). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: voltageFactor
comment: Voltage factor in pu, which was used to calculate short-circuit current Ik" and power Sk".  Used only if short circuit calculations are done according to superposition method.

label: x
comment: Reactance of device.

label: mRID
comment:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

label: b0PerSection
comment: Zero sequence shunt (charging) susceptance per section.

label: g0PerSection
comment: Zero sequence shunt (charging) conductance per section.

label: First_Terminal
comment: The starting terminal for the calculation of distances along the first branch of the mutual coupling.  Normally MutualCoupling would only be used for terminals of AC line segments.  The first and second terminals of a mutual coupling should point to different AC line segments.

label: Second_Terminal
comment: The starting terminal for the calculation of distances along the second branch of the mutual coupling.

label: b0ch
comment: Zero sequence mutual coupling shunt (charging) susceptance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

label: distance11
comment: Distance to the start of the coupled region from the first line's terminal having sequence number equal to 1.

label: distance12
comment: Distance to the end of the coupled region from the first line's terminal with sequence number equal to 1.

label: distance21
comment: Distance to the start of coupled region from the second line's terminal with sequence number equal to 1.

label: distance22
comment: Distance to the end of coupled region from the second line's terminal with sequence number equal to 1.

label: g0ch
comment: Zero sequence mutual coupling shunt (charging) conductance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

label: r0
comment: Zero sequence branch-to-branch mutual impedance coupling, resistance.

label: x0
comment: Zero sequence branch-to-branch mutual impedance coupling, reactance.

label: b0
comment: Zero sequence shunt (charging) susceptance per section.

label: g0
comment: Zero sequence shunt (charging) conductance per section.

label: mode
comment: The mode of operation of the Petersen coil.

label: nominalU
comment: The nominal voltage for which the coil is designed.

label: offsetCurrent
comment: The offset current that the Petersen coil controller is operating from the resonant point.  This is normally a fixed amount for which the controller is configured and could be positive or negative.  Typically 0 to 60 A depending on voltage and resonance conditions.

label: positionCurrent
comment: The control current used to control the Petersen coil also known as the position current.  Typically in the range of 20 mA to 200 mA.

label: xGroundMax
comment: The maximum reactance.

label: xGroundMin
comment: The minimum reactance.

label: xGroundNominal
comment: The nominal reactance.  This is the operating point (normally over compensation) that is defined based on the resonance point in the healthy network condition.  The impedance is calculated based on nominal voltage divided by position current.

label: beforeShCircuitHighestOperatingCurrent
comment: The highest operating current (Ib in IEC 60909-0) before short circuit (depends on network configuration and relevant reliability philosophy). It is used for calculation of the impedance correction factor KT defined in IEC 60909-0.

label: beforeShCircuitHighestOperatingVoltage
comment: The highest operating voltage (Ub in IEC 60909-0) before short circuit. It is used for calculation of the impedance correction factor KT defined in IEC 60909-0. This is worst case voltage on the low side winding (3.7.1 of IEC 60909:2001). Used to define operating conditions.

label: beforeShortCircuitAnglePf
comment: The angle of power factor before short circuit (phib in IEC 60909-0). It is used for calculation of the impedance correction factor KT defined in IEC 60909-0. This is the worst case power factor. Used to define operating conditions.

label: highSideMinOperatingU
comment: The minimum operating voltage (uQmin in IEC 60909-0) at the high voltage side (Q side) of the unit transformer of the power station unit. A value well established from long-term operating experience of the system. It is used for calculation of the impedance correction factor KG defined in IEC 60909-0.

label: isPartOfGeneratorUnit
comment: Indicates whether the machine is part of a power station unit. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.  It has an impact on how the correction factors are calculated for transformers, since the transformer is not necessarily part of a synchronous machine and generating unit. It is not always possible to derive this information from the model. This is why the attribute is necessary.

label: operationalValuesConsidered
comment: It is used to define if the data (other attributes related to short circuit data exchange) defines long term operational conditions or not. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: b0
comment: Zero sequence magnetizing branch susceptance.

label: g0
comment: Zero sequence magnetizing branch conductance (star-model).

label: phaseAngleClock
comment: Terminal voltage phase angle displacement where 360 degrees are represented with clock hours. The valid values are 0 to 11. For example, for the secondary side end of a transformer with vector group code of 'Dyn11', specify the connection kind as wye with neutral and specify the phase angle of the clock as 11.  The clock value of the transformer end number specified as 1, is assumed to be zero.  Note the transformer end number is not assumed to be the same as the terminal sequence number.

label: r0
comment: Zero sequence series resistance (star-model) of the transformer end.

label: x0
comment: Zero sequence series reactance of the transformer end.

label: r0
comment: Zero sequence resistance.

label: varistorPresent
comment: Describe if a metal oxide varistor (mov) for over voltage protection is configured in parallel with the series compensator. It is used for short circuit calculations.

label: varistorRatedCurrent
comment:
The maximum current the varistor is designed to handle at specified duration. It is used for short circuit calculations and exchanged only if SeriesCompensator.varistorPresent is true.
The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: varistorVoltageThreshold
comment: The dc voltage at which the varistor starts conducting. It is used for short circuit calculations and exchanged only if SeriesCompensator.varistorPresent is true.

label: x0
comment: Zero sequence reactance.

label: earthing
comment: Indicates whether or not the generator is earthed. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: earthingStarPointR
comment: Generator star point earthing resistance (Re). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: earthingStarPointX
comment: Generator star point earthing reactance (Xe). Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: ikk
comment:
Steady-state short-circuit current (in A for the profile) of generator with compound excitation during 3-phase short circuit.
- Ikk=0: Generator with no compound excitation.
- Ikk<>0: Generator with compound excitation.
Ikk is used to calculate the minimum steady-state short-circuit current for generators with compound excitation.
(4.6.1.2 in IEC 60909-0:2001).
Used only for single fed short circuit on a generator. (4.3.4.2. in IEC 60909-0:2001).

label: mu
comment:
Factor to calculate the breaking current (Section 4.5.2.1 in IEC 60909-0).
Used only for single fed short circuit on a generator (Section 4.3.4.2. in IEC 60909-0).

label: r
comment: Equivalent resistance (RG) of generator. RG is considered for the calculation of all currents, except for the calculation of the peak current ip. Used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.

label: r0
comment: Zero sequence resistance of the synchronous machine.

label: r2
comment: Negative sequence resistance.

label: satDirectSubtransX
comment: Direct-axis subtransient reactance saturated, also known as Xd"sat.

label: satDirectSyncX
comment: Direct-axes saturated synchronous reactance (xdsat); reciprocal of short-circuit ration. Used for short circuit data exchange, only for single fed short circuit on a generator. (4.3.4.2. in IEC 60909-0:2001).

label: satDirectTransX
comment: Saturated Direct-axis transient reactance. The attribute is primarily used for short circuit calculations according to ANSI.

label: shortCircuitRotorType
comment: Type of rotor, used by short circuit applications, only for single fed short circuit according to IEC 60909.

label: voltageRegulationRange
comment:
Range of generator voltage regulation (PG in IEC 60909-0) used for calculation of the impedance correction factor KG defined in IEC 60909-0.
This attribute is used to describe the operating voltage of the generating unit.

label: x0
comment: Zero sequence reactance of the synchronous machine.

label: x2
comment: Negative sequence reactance.

label: HasFirstMutualCoupling
comment: Mutual couplings associated with the branch as the first branch.

label: HasSecondMutualCoupling
comment: Mutual couplings with the branch associated as the first branch.

label: grounded
comment: (for Yn and Zn connections) True if the neutral is solidly grounded.

label: rground
comment: (for Yn and Zn connections) Resistance part of neutral impedance where 'grounded' is true.

label: xground
comment: (for Yn and Zn connections) Reactive part of neutral impedance where 'grounded' is true.
